The government is planning to announce a total of 32,000 vacancies next week as the health and education sectors set to grab lion share. This was revealed by the Minister of State in the President's Office (Public Service and Good Governance), Ms Jenister Mhagama in Parliament on Wednesday adding that State has already recruited 12,000 staff out of 44,000. “I would like to inform you that the President [Samia Suluhu Hassan] has identified the challenge of shortage of staff shortage especially in health projects and education sector…she has already  approve for employment of more staff,” the Minister parliamentarians as she added: "The government has already approved 12,000 new vacancies….next week we will announce 32,000 new jobs.” The Minister assured the general public more details regarding the recruitment process and distribution of new staff will be issued next week.